parameters: \mattHey, \N[1]! Do you know what day it is today?
\mattIt might just be the two of us, but
don't worry, I got everything that we'll
\mattI even got you this giant cake! It's
a regional specialty imported all the way
from Telluria Castle Town. It'll last
\mattBut first... I know you've been eyeing
that big stack of presents. Why don't we open
them first before you blow out the candles!
\mattFirst up is, of course, some cash!
After buying all your other gifts, I
had 100B left to give to you directly
so you can buy whatever you want.
\mattI got you a new piano book too!
\mattAw, don't give me that look. I only
want the best for you, and learning
an instrument is a great life lesson.
classics in that book! I'd love to hear
you play some while I make dinner!
\mattOf course, I got you some obligatory birthday
clothing. C'mon, everyone's gotta' get clothes
\mattBesides, you might not like it now, but
I bet you prefer this over not having
anything left to wear in a few months.
\mattI got you another import too: a few boxes of
fine chocolate from Haven Harbor! Haven is all
the way at the southern tip of Adon, and I've
heard that their chocolate is fantastic.
\mattLook, I know you wanted more than
money, a book for an instrument you
hate, clothes, and chocolate that will
run out by the end of the month.
do you have to be selfish like this?
We're already struggling to make ends
\mattI could have spent all that money
on stuff for the both of us. I could
have spent it all on myself, for
\mattI shouldn't have lashed out like that...
\mattI just let my anger get the best of
me. You're too young to... understand
\mattI'm sorry. I didn't want to make
you cry on your birthday. Today's
a day that's supposed to be about
you, after all. I feel awful.
\mattRight now, I'll give you your last
present, then you'll get to blow out
the candles. Then I'll treat you to
a day of whatever you want to do.
\mattNo... you know what? A whole week.
I get paid at the general store tonight.
After that, I'll take some time off and
we can spend the whole week together.
\mattWe can even go on another trip to
Verdin Village. Last time we went, I
think you were too young to remember...
\mattBut I need to make you feel special.
Regardless of our situation, you deserve
to feel important. Not like any of this
much, but... it has sentimental value.
\mattThese are Dad's old goggles. He'd always
wear them when he was out doing... work.
\mattHe'd always be out there with Mom. Apparently,
the bright red color was a manufacturing mistake,
but it worked out well for Dad. He said that it
helped to make sure they'd couldn't get separated.
\mattHe always did make the best out of everything...
\mattI think that you're old enough to keep
them now. They look good on you, too.
\mattI'm sure Dad would be proud to know
that you're the new owner of these.
\mattJust make sure you don't lose them, haha.
\mattThey really would be amazed by you... you're
still so young, but you're blossoming like
a beautiful flower. You'll grow up to do
great things in life, lil' bro.
\matt...ready for some cake? I'll go get the candles.
